  "about": "Madelyn Stillwell is a fictional character in the comic book series The Boys, and the television series and franchise of the same name, created by Garth Ennis and Darick Robertson. She is a high-ranking executive at Vought International who serves as the Vice President of Hero Management, acting as the handler for The Seven, including Homelander. She is a calculating and manipulative corporate figure who goes to great lengths to maintain Vought's public image and control over its superhero assets.",
